“WWE is saddened to learn that two-time WWE Hall of Famer Scott Hall has passed away. WWE extends its condolences to Hall’s family, friends and fans,” WWE wrote. Hall, who was a founding member of the New World Order faction of WWE, died on Monday, ESPN reported.  Following planned hip surgery, the WWE Champion was placed on life support after he suffered a series of heart attacks. Scott’s longtime friend, Kevin Nash, had on Monday morning, announced that Hall would be removed from life support when his family was in place. Nash wrote on his Instagram page, “Scott’s on life support. Once his family is in place, they will discontinue life support. I’m going to lose the one person on this planet I’ve spent more of my life with than anyone else. “My heart is broken and I’m so very f**king sad. I love Scott with all my heart but now I have to prepare my life without him in the present. I’ve been blessed to have a friend that took me at face value and I him.”